Student Placement Prediction using Machine Learning
Overview:
This project predicts whether a student will be placed or not based on academic performance and other factors. 
It uses Logistic Regression and ANOVA feature selection to improve model performance and interpretability.

Dataset:
Contains student academic details like SSC, HSC, degree percentage, specialization, etc.
Target variable: Placement Status (Placed / Not Placed)

Features:
Data preprocessing and cleaning
Label Encoding for categorical variables
ANOVA (F-test) feature selection
Logistic Regression model
Model evaluation using accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score

Machine Learning Workflow:
Data Loading
Data Preprocessing
Feature Selection (ANOVA)
Model Training (Logistic Regression)
Model Evaluation
Performance Comparison

Results:
Accuracy with feature selection: 76%
Accuracy without feature selection: 88%
Feature selection helped in reducing dimensionality and improving interpretability.

Key Insights:
Academic scores like SSC, HSC,Degree are strong predictors
Feature selection does not always improve accuracy but helps simplify the model
Logistic Regression performs well for binary classification problems

Tech Stack:
Python
Pandas, NumPy
Scikit-learn
Matplotlib, Seaborn
